item.title: Lipo charger button repair without soldering
item.description:
I need to remove the pcb from the case but its impossible to do without removing the original buttons, the original buttons are tight fit to the switches, when you try to pull you break the switches :(, mines are impossible to remove, tried with heat and other tricks and nothing works.

I know that this charger is the typical chinese copy that has a lot of versions with different case but same pcb, I put two versions of the buttons that you can select the one that fits with your charguer.

Mine uses two piece version.

if you have a switch with partial dmg you need to remove debris from the switch, if not the switch works glitchy… I recomend to upgrade your damage from light to full damage, clean the switch and use the bigger buttons.

You can see that the screw can fit below the case, this is important.

Recomend to print this in ASA or ABS due high temperatures that charger reaches, the top buttons of 2 piece version you can print in TPU.

item.title: Dice Pyramid - Camel Up - Improved Fitting Top
item.description:
The original tower is really nice. You dont have to turn the pyramid upside down in order to roll a die.

The STL for the top of the original has a tolerance of 0,2mm (24,8mm Top for 25mm hole in Mid). On my Prusa MINI I have rather high precision, so the top is rattling and can fall off easily.

My STL for the top is 25mm wide in order to fit the 25mm hole. The original is 24,8mm.

Also, I highly recommend to not print the Mid section upside down, as recommended by the original author: The overhanging edges are going to look more rough than on the other parts, that are printed in the correct dimension. Print the Mid section in the correct orientation and add supports on the build plate instead.

TL;DR:

  • My Top fits better when the printer is very accurate.
  • Print the Mid not upside down. Add supports instead.

item.title: Drawer slide for under table
item.description:
I wanted to add a drawer under a 3d printer for tools. This was made to cut 2.5" pine trim for the walls of the drawer with a masonite bottom. The 2 part tracks total about and 18" deep drawer and as wide as you want. Because the printer could not print a bracket that long I made the track in 2 halves with the keys. Once the bracket is screwed under the table it will not move but you can add a dab of crazy glue to the keys when you put them in if you like.

Obviously you will need to print two of each parts and 4 keys.

item.title: LED-Beleuchtung Anycubic Mega X
item.description:
Thank you Hiob for your Post. I took your idea and created a new designet variant of it.

I used 12V "YourLED Eco Basic" by Paulmann and some electronic stuff for the switch.
I choosed 12V because I also could connect the LED-Light also with the power adapter of the printer.

But I read many post, that the power adapter of the Mega X is sometimes a little weak. So I preferred to connect it with the normal power connection.

I also created little connectors at the profiles ends to be sure that the profiles are at the right place.

I hope you will like my LED-Holder-Remake for the Anycubic Mega X.
